What is Linux Shell?
A shell provide an environment to a user to execute commands and interact with kernal.There are different types of shell:
->bash          ->tsh
->sh            ->fish
->ksh           ->zsh

what is current shell type?
echo $0
cat /etc/shells
bash

What is Shell scripting?
->Shall script consist of set of commands to perform a task.
->All the commands execute sequentially.
->Some task like file manipulation, program execution, user interaction, automation of task etc can be done.

Creating first shell scripting.
#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello world!"
commands:
vi filename   ex: vi 01_bash_shell
i for insert ; esc ; shift+ ; :wq

what is shebang?
#!/bin/bash

sending output to terminal...
echo "Hello world!"

How to run a script?
bash script_name
ls -ltr
chmod u+x script_name     [Execute permission rw-r--r--]
      (or)
->Make sure script has execute permission rwx
->Run using
      ./script.sh
      /path/script.sh
      bash script.sh
->ctrl+c to terminate.
->ctrl+z to stop
/root/script/script_name   (or) bash /root/script/script_name
